07-18-14

NOTE
current installation and running was only tested on Mavericks (OSX 10.9.1), but it is expected to work on any UNIX/LINUX-based machines

DEPENDENCIES
you only need to install gcc with c++11 support

DIRECTORY LAYOUT
./src: source codes (.cpp files)
./include: header files (.h files)
./test: testing directory where the executable will be generated; data also stays here

COMPILING AND RUNNING INSTRUCTIONS
(1) At the current directory, type:
make
(2) Go to the "test" directory, type:
./a.out
